{
  "local_port": 32916,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the postings under SSC?",
  "response": "The **Staff Selection Commission (SSC)** is an organization under the Government of India that conducts various examinations to recruit staff for different posts in ministries, departments, and organizations of the Government of India. The SSC offers a wide range of job opportunities across various sectors. Below is an overview of the primary **postings under SSC**, categorized by the examinations they conduct:\n\n---\n\n## 1. **SSC Combined Graduate Level (CGL)**\n\nThe **SSC CGL** examination is one of the most popular exams conducted by SSC to recruit candidates for various Group B and Group C posts in different Ministries, Departments, and Organizations of the Government of India.\n\n### **Postings Under SSC CGL:**\n1. **Assistant Section Officer (ASO)**\n2. **Assistant Examiner**\n3. **Income Tax Inspector**\n4. **Assistant Audit Officer**\n5. **Assistant Enforcement Officer (AEO)**\n6. **Central Excise Inspector**\n7. **Assistant Commercial Apprentice**\n8. **Sub-Inspectors (Various Ministries)**\n9. **Tourism Coordinator**\n10. **Statistician**\n11. **Junior Secretariat Assistant**\n12. **Tax Assistant**\n13. **Commercial Apprentice**\n14. **Librarian**\n15. **Audit and Accounts Assistant**\n16. **Assistant Commandant (For certain posts)**\n17. **Assistant in Departments like DRDO, ISRO, etc. (Technical Posts)**\n   \n---\n\n## 2. **SSC Combined Higher Secondary Level (CHSL)**\n\nThe **SSC CHSL** exam is conducted to recruit candidates for various posts at the entry-level, primarily in the ministries and departments of the Government of India.\n\n### **Postings Under SSC CHSL:**\n1. **Lower Divisional Clerk (LDC)**\n2. **Data Entry Operator (DEO)**\n3. **Postal Assistant / Sorting Assistant**\n4. **Court Clerk**\n5. **Steno Technician**\n6. **Jr. Secretariat Assistant (JSA)**\n7. **Assistant in various Ministries and Departments**\n8. **Office Assistant**\n9. **Records and Stenographer Grade II**\n10. **Dispatcher**\n   \n---\n\n## 3. **SSC Junior Engineer (JE)**\n\nThe **SSC JE** exam is conducted to recruit Junior Engineers in different engineering disciplines for various government departments.\n\n### **Postings Under SSC JE:**\n1. **Junior Engineer Civil**\n2. **Junior Engineer Electrical**\n3. **Junior Engineer Mechanical**\n4. **Junior Engineer Quantity Surveyors & Contracts**\n5. **Junior Engineer Electronics & Telecommunication**\n6. **Junior Engineer Planning & Estimation**\n7. **Junior Engineer Chemical**\n8. **Junior Engineer Electronics**\n   \n---\n\n## 4. **SSC Combined Police Examination (CPO & DI)**\n\nThe **SSC CPO** and **SSC DI** are conducted for recruitment to various police forces.\n\n### **Postings Under SSC CPO:**\n1. **Sub-Inspector (SI) in Central Armed Police Forces (CAPFs) like BSF, CISF, CRPF, etc.)**\n2. **Assistant Sub-Inspector (ASI)**\n3. **Lower Division Clerk (LDC)**\n4. **Constable**\n\n### **Postings Under SSC DI:**\n1. **Detective Inspector (DI) in various CSI (Crime Scene Investigation) Wing of Indian Police Service**\n   \n---\n\n## 5. **SSC Multi-Tasking Staff (MTS)**\n\nThe **SSC MTS** exam is conducted to recruit Multi-Tasking Staff across various government offices.\n\n### **Postings Under SSC MTS:**\n1. **Sweeper**\n2. **Driver**\n3. **Helper**\n4. **Peon**\n5. **Watchman**\n6. **Guard**\n7. **Cleaner**\n8. **Laboratory Assistant**\n   \n---\n\n## 6. **SSC Stenographer (Grade C & D)**\n\nThe **SSC Stenographer** exam is conducted to recruit stenographers for various government departments.\n\n### **Postings Under SSC Stenographer:**\n1. **Stenograph Grade C**\n2. **Grade D Stenographer**\n   \n---\n\n## 7. **SSC Registered Apprentices (RA)**\n\nThe **SSC RA** exam is for recruiting candidates as apprentices in various government offices.\n\n### **Postings Under SSC RA:**\n1. **Electrical Apprentice**\n2. **Mechanical Apprentice**\n3. **Civil Apprentice**\n4. **Hardware Apprentice**\n5. **Other Technical Apprenticeships**\n   \n---\n\n## 8. **SSC Special Class Railway Apprentice (SCRA)**\n\nAlthough recently replaced by other recruitment processes, the **SSC SCRA** was conducted for recruiting apprentices in the Railway sector.\n\n### **Postings Under SSC SCRA:**\n1. **Apprentices in various trades like Permanent Way, Civil, Electrical, Mechanical, etc.)**\n   \n---\n\n## 9. **SSC National Council for Rotary Sphere of the Year Award (NCRSWron Award)**\n\nThis is a less common posting and is specific to certain awards and recognitions.\n\n---\n\n## 10. **SSC Specialist Roles and Technical Posts**\n\nIn addition to the above, SSC also recruits for specialized technical and support roles in various government departments such as:\n\n1. **Technical Assistant**\n2. **Scientific Assistant**\n3. **Library Assistant**\n4. **Accounts Assistant**\n5. **Surveyor**\n\n---\n\n## **Key Points to Remember:**\n\n- **Eligibility:** Each SSC examination has specific eligibility criteria regarding educational qualifications, age limits, and other requirements. It's essential to check the official SSC notification for detailed eligibility criteria.\n  \n- **Examination Structure:** Most SSC exams, like SSC CGL and SSC CHSL, comprise multiple tiers, including preliminary exams, mains exams, and typing tests or skill tests.\n\n- **Application Process:** Applications are generally submitted online through the [official SSC website](https://ssc.nic.in/). Candidates should be cautious of fraudulent websites and adhere strictly to official notifications.\n\n- **Preparation:** Given the competitive nature of SSC exams, thorough preparation, regular practice, and staying updated with current affairs are crucial for success.\n\n---\n\nFor the most accurate and detailed information, including the latest updates on recruitment, eligibility, and application procedures, always refer to the [official SSC website](https://ssc.nic.in/) or the specific exam notifications released by SSC.",
